%I A396988 #13 Jun 16 2026 20:03:46
%S A396988 1,2,8,75,1342,38828,1710403
%N A396988 Number of convexities on an n set induced by preorders.
%C A396988 A convexity C on a set X is a collection of subsets of X such that {} and X are in C, C is closed under arbitrary intersection, and C is closed under directed union. A preorder <= on X induces the convexity of convex subsets of X, where a subset S of X is said to be convex if z in A for all x,y in S and z in X with x<=z<=y.
%D A396988 Davey, Brian A., and Hilary A. Priestley. Introduction to Lattices and Order. 2nd ed. Cambridge Mathematical Textbooks. Cambridge: Cambridge University Press, 2002.
%D A396988 M. L. J. van de Vel, Theory of Convex Structures, North-Holland Mathematical Library, vol. 50, North-Holland, Amsterdam, 1993.
%H A396988 Tian Vlasic, <a href="/A396988/a396988.py.txt">Python program</a>
%F A396988 Every convexity on a set X induced by a preorder <= is an interval convexity (see A364656), with intervals given by I(x,y)={z in X: x<=z<=y}, so a(n)<=A364656(n).
%e A396988 a(3)=8 as there are 8 convexities on X={a,b,c} induced by preorders:
%e A396988   {{},{a,b,c}}
%e A396988   {{},{a},{b,c},{a,b,c}}
%e A396988   {{},{b},{a,c},{a,b,c}}
%e A396988   {{},{c},{a,b},{a,b,c}}
%e A396988   {{},{a},{b},{c},{a,b},{a,c},{a,b,c}}
%e A396988   {{},{a},{b},{c},{a,b},{b,c},{a,b,c}}
%e A396988   {{},{a},{b},{c},{a,c},{b,c},{a,b,c}}
%e A396988   {{},{a},{b},{c},{a,b},{a,c},{b,c},{a,b,c}}
%Y A396988 Cf. A102894, A364656, A367422.
%K A396988 nonn,more,new
